> There's a man called Rhyan and that man loves potatoes more than anything in the world. He once ate 45 roast potatoes in one sitting - and no we just don't know how! Anyway, he's one lucky guy because he's our chef Mimi's flatmate and she always makes extra potato salad just for him at their barbecues. This dish is from Mimi to her pal Rhyan - because it's his favourite version of potato salad and can be eaten all year round! Enjoy Mimi's pan-fried tilapia and Rhyan's warm potato salad.

Bring a #large pot{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Chop the @potato{2}(chopped into roughly 3cm pieces). Chop the @chives{5}(chopped into roughly 1cm pieces, use scissors if you have them) into roughly 1cm pieces (use scissors if you have them!) Remove the root from the @spring greens{6}(sliced and root removed) and finely slice them.

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook for ~{15-20%mins} or until soft.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily stick a knife through them.

When they're cooked, drain them and put them back in their #pot{}. Crush them slightly with a #fork{} and then add in the @crème fraîche{1}, @wholegrain mustard{1}, and chopped chives along with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Mix everything together, then put a lid on the pot and leave to the side.

In the meantime, peel and finely chop the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and finely chopped).

Put the @flour{2} in a #bowl{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Add your @tilapia fillet{4} to the bowl and give the bowl a shake so the fish all has a coating of flour.

Put @oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the spring greens along with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Cook for ~{2%mins} before adding the chopped garlic. Cook for another ~{1%minute}. Then take the spring greens out of the pan and set aside while you cook the fish.

> You may need two pans to do this.

Add another @oil{2%tbsp} to the frying pan and add the fish fillets. Cook for ~{3%mins} on one side before turning over and cooking for ~{2%mins} on the other side.

> Only turn them once in this time!

Serve your fish with your garlicky spring greens and warm potato salad on the side.